4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would create a workforce talent
6 recruitment program, administered by the Alabama
7 Department of Economic and Community Affairs, to award
8 grants for incentivizing individuals and households to
9 relocate to this state.
10 This bill would designate that eligible
11 applicants for the program are municipalities,
12 counties, and nonprofit organizations.
13 This bill would provide an application process
14 for eligible applicants to apply for grant funds under
15 the program.
16 This bill would provide data reporting
17 requirements for grant recipients.
18 This bill would provide eligibility requirements
19 for individuals and households to receive relocation
20 incentives under the program.
21 This bill would also create the Talent
22 Recruitment Program Grant Fund to provide for the
23 administration and disbursement of grant funds.
24
25
26 A BILL
27 TO BE ENTITLED
28 AN ACT
Page 1

AN ACT
HB354 INTRODUCED
29
30 Relating to the Department of Economic and Community
31 Affairs and workforce talent recruitment; to establish a
32 talent recruitment grant program administered by the
33 department; to award grant funds to eligible applicants; to
34 provide eligibility standards; and to establish the Talent
35 Recruitment Program Grant Fund.
36 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
37 Section 1. For the purposes of this act, the following
38 terms have the following meanings:
39 (1) DEPARTMENT. The Department of Economic and
40 Community Affairs.
41 (2) HOUSEHOLD. A group of one or more individuals who
42 dwell together within the same dwelling.
43 (3) HOUSEHOLD GOAL. The total number of households that
44 a talent recruitment program seeks to successfully incentivize
45 to relocate or commit to relocate from outside this state to a
46 municipality in this state.
47 Section 2. (a) Subject to the availability of funds,
48 the department shall:
49 (1) Establish and administer a workforce talent
50 recruitment grant program for the purpose of awarding grants
51 for talent recruitment programs that incentivize households to
52 relocate from outside this state to a municipality in this
53 state;
54 (2) Award grants to eligible applicants for the purpose
55 of administering the talent recruitment program and the costs
56 associated with incentivizing households to relocate from
Page 2

associated with incentivizing households to relocate from
HB354 INTRODUCED
57 outside the state to municipalities in the state; and
58 (3) Disburse 50 percent of the total grant award upon
59 entering into a grant contract and 50 percent of the total
60 grant award upon the recipient reporting to the department
61 that the recipient has successfully met half of the household
62 goal stated in the talent recruitment program plan. If the
63 recipient fails to meet half of its stated household goal, the
64 department shall not disburse the remaining grant amount.
65 (b) Eligible applicants for the talent recruitment
66 program shall include:
67 (1) A municipality or county in this state; and
68 (2) A nonprofit organization that has as a mission
69 economic development, workforce and talent development, or
70 community development.
71 (c) Applicants for the talent recruitment program shall
72 do all of the following:
73 (1) Provide the department with a talent recruitment
74 program plan that includes:
75 a. The total estimated cost of the program;
76 b. The individual estimated costs associated with the
77 program's design, administration, marketing, and relocation
78 incentive initiatives;
79 c. The program's household goal;
80 d. The estimated total grant amount per relocated
81 household;
82 e. The program's estimated state and local tax impact;
83 and
84 f. The program's estimated total economic impact.
Page 3

f. The program's estimated total economic impact.
HB354 INTRODUCED
85 (2) Demonstrate the ability to contribute at least 20
86 percent of the total talent recruitment program cost. The
87 applicant's contribution may include local investments and
88 in-kind donations. In order for a previous grant recipient to
89 be eligible for additional grant funds, the applicant must
90 have met the household goal stated in the talent recruitment
91 program plan.
92 (d) Each grant recipient must provide semiannual
93 reports to the department with the following information:
94 (1) The total number of household applications.
95 (2) The total number of approved households.
96 (3) The cost per approved household.
97 (4) The annual incomes and occupations of approved
98 households.
99 (5) The economic impact of the talent recruitment
100 program, including state and local tax revenue and new
101 consumer spending.
102 (6) Verification of eligibility for moved and committed
103 to move households.
104 (e) A household is eligible for the talent recruitment
105 program incentives if the household meets all of the following
106 requirements:
107 (1) Resides outside of this state at the time the
108 household applies for talent recruitment program incentives.
109 (2) Has an individual household income of at least
110 fifty five thousand dollars ($55,000).
111 (3) Submits an application to the recipient of a grant
112 to receive talent recruitment program incentives.
