113 Section 3. (a) The Talent Recruitment Program Grant
114 Fund is created in the State Treasury.
115 (b) The fund shall consist of all monies paid into the
116 State Treasury to the credit of the fund or by legislative
117 appropriations, grants, gifts, or otherwise.
118 (c) Monies contained in the fund may be expended for
119 grants as provided under this act.
120 (d) At the end of any fiscal year, any unexpended or
121 unencumbered monies contributed to or deposited in the fund
122 from any source shall remain in the fund for the use of the
123 department for the talent recruitment program.
124 (e) All monies in the fund shall be budgeted and
125 allotted pursuant to the Budget Management Act in accordance
126 with Article 4 of Chapter 4 and Chapter 19 of Title 41, Code
127 of Alabama 1975, and only in the amount provided by the
128 Legislature in the general appropriations act or other
129 appropriations act.
130 Section 4. This act shall become effective on October
131 1, 2026.
